00:26.467 --> 00:28.001
Where are you going?

02:00.759 --> 02:03.594
This isn't yellow fever. This is smallpox.

02:03.595 --> 02:05.424
I know.

02:05.425 --> 02:09.461
And you didn't think this was
important information for me to have?

02:09.463 --> 02:11.463
Yellow fever is common.

02:12.799 --> 02:15.393
Rest of the world will not even notice.

02:15.394 --> 02:17.328
But smallpox,

02:17.430 --> 02:20.899
would you buy beef or coffee
beans from a country with that?

02:20.900 --> 02:23.602
But I could have brought the vaccine.

02:23.603 --> 02:25.737
Medicines.

02:25.738 --> 02:27.873
I'm equipped for the wrong disease.

02:29.876 --> 02:32.343
You will do as you're told.

02:32.512 --> 02:36.313
After all, it was your country that
caused this outbreak in the first place.

02:58.669 --> 03:00.504
Are you American?

03:01.672 --> 03:04.541
Help me. Help me.

03:12.384 --> 03:14.018
John Thackery, Philadelphia.

03:14.019 --> 03:15.751
August Robertson, New York.

03:15.752 --> 03:17.520
I know the name.

03:17.521 --> 03:19.088
What are you doing here?

03:19.089 --> 03:20.789
I'm a doctor.

03:20.790 --> 03:22.558
I was working the Mosquito Coast.

03:22.559 --> 03:24.560
They called me in for this.

03:24.728 --> 03:28.130
This is the last place I expected
to see a man from the society pages.

03:28.232 --> 03:30.733
My shipping company, they
use Nicaragua as a shortcut

03:30.767 --> 03:32.735
to the West Coast and the Orient and back.

03:32.802 --> 03:34.870
Two weeks crossing this
country saves me two months

03:34.905 --> 03:37.840
in navigation around South America.

03:37.874 --> 03:40.342
So why are they keeping you prisoner?

03:40.476 --> 03:43.846
Are you the American that's supposed
to have caused this outbreak?

03:43.947 --> 03:46.248
My shipping company pays
them in trinkets and blankets

03:46.315 --> 03:48.450
and now they're saying those
blankets made them sick.

03:48.451 --> 03:50.786
That's very possible.

03:50.787 --> 03:52.587
They killed 12 of my men.

03:52.622 --> 03:53.822
Mostly Hondurans.

03:53.890 --> 03:55.690
And they're gonna kill
me, I can assure you.

03:55.792 --> 03:57.759
Please, you've got to help me. Ah!

03:57.761 --> 03:59.527
You need to let the American go.

03:59.595 --> 04:02.964
He will pay for this disease with his life.

04:02.998 --> 04:05.133
But you can't be sure he's responsible.

04:05.134 --> 04:06.801
He stays.

04:08.637 --> 04:11.806
Well, then I won't cure these people.

04:11.840 --> 04:13.975
Then you will end up
like your American friend.

04:15.311 --> 04:16.711
If this thing spreads,

04:16.745 --> 04:18.644
it's the most contagious
thing on the Earth.

04:18.680 --> 04:21.548
You let him go, I will save these people.

04:27.489 --> 04:30.091
Without the vaccine?

04:30.092 --> 04:32.426
I have a way.

05:17.971 --> 05:19.938
These are the survivors.

05:19.972 --> 05:21.873
They can no longer get the disease.

05:21.874 --> 05:23.507
They're immune.

05:23.575 --> 05:26.510
So they can help us with
those who still have it.

05:26.578 --> 05:30.048
Tell them to wrap these
bandages around the skin.

05:30.049 --> 05:33.151
It will help their sores heal.

05:54.005 --> 05:55.839
For those who haven't gotten the disease,

05:55.840 --> 05:57.907
this will keep them safe.

05:57.909 --> 05:59.543
They'll get a mild case of it.

05:59.544 --> 06:01.778
They'll definitely recover

06:01.779 --> 06:04.013
and they'll never get it again.

06:04.014 --> 06:06.082
Even if this does work,

06:06.083 --> 06:07.884
I'm still keeping his cargo.

06:15.389 --> 06:19.655
<b>Subtitle sync and corrections
by awaqeded for www.addic7ed.com.</b>

06:56.599 --> 06:58.599
Girls, you ready?

08:05.833 --> 08:08.601
Good morning, Dr. Gallinger.

08:11.471 --> 08:13.572
Detective.

08:13.573 --> 08:15.774
What can I do for you?

08:15.875 --> 08:19.478
I had some more information
regarding Dr. Cotton's death

08:19.512 --> 08:21.480
that you might be interested in hearing

08:21.580 --> 08:25.150
since, as you said, you and
your wife were so fond of him.

08:27.653 --> 08:29.454
Would you follow me?

08:33.159 --> 08:34.926
What is it?

08:35.028 --> 08:39.063
We've confirmed that he was
most definitely poisoned.

08:39.065 --> 08:41.899
And we now know who did it.

08:44.169 --> 08:46.103
You do?

08:46.104 --> 08:48.873
You might want to prepare yourself.

08:50.575 --> 08:52.909
It was his sons who did him in.

08:52.911 --> 08:55.112
They both were studying at Princeton

08:55.247 --> 08:58.815
and were slowly adding arsenic
to their father's meals over time.

09:02.054 --> 09:03.855
You're positive about this?

09:03.856 --> 09:05.556
They confessed it.

09:05.590 --> 09:07.591
They were surprised he had died so quickly

09:07.759 --> 09:11.295
since, as they said, they had only
been adding the arsenic a short while.

09:11.363 --> 09:13.597
Must have given him
more than they realized.

09:13.598 --> 09:15.466
Not that I blame them.

09:15.533 --> 09:19.002
From what I gather, the old man was a nut.

09:20.438 --> 09:21.872
You know that crazy man

09:21.874 --> 09:24.275
pulled the teeth out of their head.

09:26.211 --> 09:28.879
His own children's teeth.

09:28.914 --> 09:31.248
Why the hell do you do something like that?

09:33.217 --> 09:35.552
He thought it would keep them sane.

09:37.989 --> 09:40.656
Have the boys been arrested?

09:40.657 --> 09:43.859
They killed themselves before we could.

09:43.928 --> 09:47.430
So I guess Daddy's treatment
didn't work out so great.

09:49.100 --> 09:51.467
Anyway, just thought you'd want to know.

09:51.468 --> 09:53.569
Thank you.

09:53.570 --> 09:55.538
How's your wife?

09:57.474 --> 09:59.075
Doing well.

09:59.076 --> 10:01.244
Give her my best.

10:21.831 --> 10:24.132
Will you excuse us for a moment, Dudley?

10:25.868 --> 10:27.802
Thank you.

10:29.806 --> 10:31.740
Your mother said you're leaving.

10:32.875 --> 10:35.110
Going to Ohio tonight.

10:35.111 --> 10:37.379
The refinery is nearly ready.

10:37.480 --> 10:39.648
Talking with some men in
Cleveland and up near Detroit

10:39.715 --> 10:42.951
about using our gasoline
for automotive propulsion.

10:42.953 --> 10:45.320
Well, when will you be back?

10:46.722 --> 10:49.023
Do you really care?

10:49.024 --> 10:50.658
Of course.

10:50.660 --> 10:52.761
'Cause I want you to come with me.

10:52.862 --> 10:55.230
It's a part of my father's
business that could be mine.

10:55.297 --> 10:58.833
I can build it. We can make a life there.

10:58.835 --> 11:02.036
Phillip, it's a lot all at once.

11:02.037 --> 11:03.504
I need some time.

11:03.539 --> 11:06.374
No, I don't want words or protestations.

11:06.408 --> 11:09.210
It's not what you say, it's what you do.

11:09.311 --> 11:12.480
I'm leaving tonight. I
don't know when I'll be back.

11:12.515 --> 11:14.682
Now either you're coming
with me, your husband,

11:14.683 --> 11:16.584
to be with me wherever we end up,

11:16.585 --> 11:18.419
or you're not.

11:18.520 --> 11:23.024
And if you're not, I'll
find someone who wants to.

11:23.025 --> 11:25.225
I deserve at least that.

11:41.210 --> 11:43.310
May I come in?

11:51.919 --> 11:54.321
How are you doing?

11:59.894 --> 12:03.663
I'm deeply sorry, John.

12:06.367 --> 12:08.234
What did you want?

12:10.371 --> 12:13.140
Just wanted to give you
a report on the twins.

12:13.141 --> 12:15.842
Some good news for a change.

12:17.444 --> 12:20.446
Dr. Chickering and I
examined them this morning.

12:20.447 --> 12:22.514
Nika's pneumonia has receded.

12:24.317 --> 12:27.786
The amount of albumin in
their urine has decreased.

12:27.788 --> 12:30.957
They're eating full meals and...

12:30.958 --> 12:33.092
they took their first steps alone.

12:35.796 --> 12:37.363
Also, the orphanage informs me

12:37.464 --> 12:39.866
that a family from Missouri
has agreed to take the girls.

12:39.900 --> 12:41.433
They arrived in the city yesterday

12:41.501 --> 12:44.737
and are just waiting on
our approval to let them go.

12:44.738 --> 12:46.438
I think they're ready.

12:47.775 --> 12:49.775
Sounds like it.

12:53.447 --> 12:55.614
Congratulations.

13:31.350 --> 13:34.219
So, here's what I'm thinking.

13:34.220 --> 13:37.588
We start at the East Side piers.

13:37.690 --> 13:40.125
Find some sailors coming
back from a long time at sea

13:40.126 --> 13:41.727
looking to get their logs dunked.

13:41.728 --> 13:44.195
Then we head to 29th Street.

13:44.396 --> 13:47.966
They've got enough brothels and dance
halls to keep us selling till Christmas.

13:47.967 --> 13:49.935
Fine.

13:52.204 --> 13:54.705
How long you gonna be sore with me?

13:54.706 --> 13:56.874
As long as I feel like.

13:56.908 --> 13:59.544
I may not be a nun
anymore, but I took my vows,

13:59.545 --> 14:01.912
vows that you know I intend on keeping.

14:01.913 --> 14:04.215
It was one little kiss, all right?

14:04.216 --> 14:05.883
A kiss I didn't even get.

14:05.884 --> 14:07.685
You're a hound,

14:07.719 --> 14:09.820
like all them fellas getting off the boats

14:09.821 --> 14:11.856
looking to get their logs dunked.

14:11.990 --> 14:15.159
I can't trust you now just like
I shouldn't have all this time.

14:16.094 --> 14:19.531
I got carried away is all.

14:19.532 --> 14:22.166
Because what I said is true.

14:23.935 --> 14:25.836
I do have feelings for you.

14:29.374 --> 14:31.976
Then I'd ask you to please
keep them to yourself.

14:33.545 --> 14:36.613
This box is ready.

14:36.715 --> 14:39.383
Guess those vows didn't
include one of forgiveness.

14:39.384 --> 14:40.718
What?

14:40.719 --> 14:42.419
Nothing, all right? I'm sorry.

14:42.520 --> 14:45.055
I didn't mean to tempt you
into breaking your vows.

14:45.057 --> 14:47.257
Believe me, a gorilla like you,

14:47.258 --> 14:49.659
there wasn't the least bit of temptation.

15:05.409 --> 15:07.410
Mr. Jenkins.

15:07.411 --> 15:08.711
Herman Barrow.

15:08.713 --> 15:09.879
Good to meet you, Mr. Barrow.

15:09.880 --> 15:11.581
And you, sir.

15:11.582 --> 15:13.149
- Shall we?
- Yes.

15:27.063 --> 15:28.664
Thank you, Mr. Barrow.

15:28.665 --> 15:30.599
Welcome to the Metropolitan Club.

15:47.250 --> 15:49.517
I "don'ts" know what a Vander is,

15:49.518 --> 15:51.485
but I'm sho glad he done built it.

15:51.487 --> 15:53.855
Herman, how are you?

15:53.856 --> 15:55.757
I'm very well, Corky, thank you.

15:55.758 --> 15:57.158
That was a wonderful evening.

15:57.159 --> 15:58.826
Please.

15:58.827 --> 16:00.728
Oh.

16:00.829 --> 16:04.666
Well, we very much appreciated
your generous donation.

16:04.667 --> 16:06.801
Ah.

16:17.512 --> 16:19.112
Dr. Thackery?

16:21.316 --> 16:24.952
Dr. Thackery, it's Nurse Baker.

16:25.019 --> 16:27.520
The twins are leaving. I
thought you'd want to know.

16:47.641 --> 16:49.910
Where is Dr. Thackery?

16:49.911 --> 16:51.978
We want to say good-bye.

16:52.013 --> 16:53.846
I'm sure he wishes he could be here,

16:53.848 --> 16:57.450
but unfortunately he's elsewhere.

17:01.988 --> 17:03.723
Be well, girls.

17:12.366 --> 17:13.733
Finally, a good outcome.

17:13.733 --> 17:15.467
Yeah.

17:17.737 --> 17:20.939
Oh, well, I don't suppose he's rushing over

17:20.940 --> 17:23.107
for one last wave at the twins.

17:23.108 --> 17:25.009
You brought me up on charges?

17:25.010 --> 17:26.444
What?

17:26.445 --> 17:28.079
I've been called to defend myself

17:28.079 --> 17:30.081
in front of the state medical board.

17:30.082 --> 17:32.050
You sterilized idiots?

17:32.051 --> 17:33.685
Dozens.

17:33.686 --> 17:36.521
I had no idea how far outside

17:36.588 --> 17:38.455
the brotherhood of
physicians you were until now.

17:38.457 --> 17:40.190
And I had no idea how far outside you were

17:40.191 --> 17:41.859
until you sabotaged me.

17:41.860 --> 17:43.961
How?

17:43.962 --> 17:46.230
The Carr surgery.

17:46.231 --> 17:47.965
I know it was you.

17:48.099 --> 17:50.100
Why? Because there's no chance
you would ever make a mistake?

17:50.235 --> 17:53.203
No, because there is no chance that
you are a better doctor than I am.

17:53.238 --> 17:56.405
Oh, for God's sake. Shut up, both of you.

17:56.440 --> 17:58.407
Everett, you're supposed to be on the ward.

18:00.745 --> 18:03.312
Have I missed the twins?

18:03.313 --> 18:04.947
Just.

18:04.948 --> 18:06.383
They asked after you.

18:08.586 --> 18:09.719
Thack! Thack!

18:09.720 --> 18:11.788
Quick, quick, fetch a gurney.

18:11.789 --> 18:13.222
No.

18:13.223 --> 18:14.223
You have been in pain for weeks.

18:14.224 --> 18:15.557
You need to be examined.

18:15.558 --> 18:18.293
You mean opened up? Like hell.

18:18.395 --> 18:20.862
All right, well, maybe
there's another alternative.

18:59.367 --> 19:01.468
Have a look, doctors.

19:05.607 --> 19:07.441
My Lord.

19:07.543 --> 19:11.979
You do realize the patient is
conscious, don't you, Bertie?

19:11.980 --> 19:15.415
I was marveling at the technology.

19:16.952 --> 19:19.153
Zinberg taught you to tell the truth.

19:19.154 --> 19:21.588
I taught you to lie.

19:21.622 --> 19:24.991
Seems like neither of
us did a very good job.

19:24.993 --> 19:27.461
It is a marvelous invention.

19:27.462 --> 19:28.995
And what does it tell you?

19:29.030 --> 19:31.531
That a section of your bowel is ischemic.

19:31.532 --> 19:33.533
Agreed.

19:34.702 --> 19:37.337
I suppose we can guess what's caused it.

19:37.372 --> 19:39.073
Well, we don't need to get into that.

19:39.074 --> 19:41.107
No, that's all right.

19:41.142 --> 19:43.710
A man ingests cocaine for long enough,

19:43.845 --> 19:47.212
then his intestinal blood
vessels don't stand a chance.

19:48.682 --> 19:51.049
You'll need a resection.

19:51.051 --> 19:54.453
Is the entire intestine necrotic?

19:56.056 --> 19:59.158
Well, we can only guess
from what little we can see,

19:59.193 --> 20:01.560
but I'll schedule surgery
as soon as possible.

20:01.561 --> 20:04.763
No, I want to find an alternative.

20:04.764 --> 20:07.166
What do you mean?

20:07.167 --> 20:09.535
I don't want to rush into it.

20:10.704 --> 20:14.040
There are other things I want to try.

20:14.041 --> 20:15.508
Medications.

20:15.509 --> 20:17.742
You collapsed on the street.

20:17.743 --> 20:20.278
Your bowel looks like the badlands.

20:20.279 --> 20:21.746
What more evidence do you need?

20:21.747 --> 20:23.648
No medication is gonna repair that.

20:23.682 --> 20:27.719
Yet it is not for any of you to decide.

20:27.887 --> 20:32.056
Ladies, I am kindly asking you
to please stay out of my way.

20:32.058 --> 20:34.659
I will go wherever I please.

20:34.760 --> 20:38.763
These nurses are saying I
am barred from the building.

20:40.099 --> 20:44.202
You need to make an
appointment like everyone else.

20:44.203 --> 20:46.938
I am not everyone else.

20:49.042 --> 20:52.276
Thank you, nurses. Everything is fine.

20:53.712 --> 20:55.912
Please close the door.

21:02.154 --> 21:04.121
How's your whore?

21:04.122 --> 21:05.622
Is she well?

21:05.623 --> 21:07.425
Junia is very well.

21:07.426 --> 21:09.460
Thank you.

21:09.461 --> 21:11.328
And how's your new apartment?

21:11.329 --> 21:13.597
Tiny and awful, I trust?

21:13.598 --> 21:15.899
Actually, that's why I'm here.

21:15.967 --> 21:20.404
I want you to buy me a
big, nice one with a view

21:20.405 --> 21:23.474
like yours for me and the children.

21:23.475 --> 21:26.176
Preferably on the Upper East Side.

21:26.244 --> 21:29.913
In a dream, that might
be something I would do.

21:29.914 --> 21:32.282
By law, I owe you nothing.

21:45.162 --> 21:47.129
What is that?

21:47.198 --> 21:50.966
Apparently, it's the actual amount of steel

21:50.968 --> 21:52.469
that was delivered to the new Knick

21:52.470 --> 21:55.070
on March 4, 1901.

21:55.139 --> 21:57.707
I'm assuming that
somewhere in this building

21:57.841 --> 22:01.076
there's a document claiming that
the delivery was much greater,

22:01.212 --> 22:04.380
as was the amount that you
required the hospital to pay for it.

22:04.482 --> 22:08.618
We'll both just suppose we
know where the extra money went.

22:08.619 --> 22:10.653
Where did you get that?

22:10.654 --> 22:12.754
You keep excellent records, Herman.

22:12.855 --> 22:15.323
And you were very smart to
keep them out of the hospital

22:15.325 --> 22:17.358
where people could find them.

22:17.460 --> 22:21.329
Unfortunately, when I went
to the bank the other day

22:21.464 --> 22:25.400
to retrieve jewelry from my
safe-deposit box to sell it,

22:25.401 --> 22:28.337
the banker mistakenly gave me the keys

22:28.338 --> 22:31.440
to the other Barrow box.

22:33.343 --> 22:35.544
Where are they now, the papers?

22:35.545 --> 22:38.347
In a new safe-deposit box.

22:38.348 --> 22:40.348
They're all there...

22:40.349 --> 22:42.016
everything you did

22:42.017 --> 22:44.351
and every penny you stole.

22:46.688 --> 22:49.156
What do you want?

22:49.224 --> 22:52.993
I want to live the life I
was accustomed to living.

22:53.028 --> 22:56.830
I want the children back in their schools.

22:56.831 --> 22:59.933
I want the apartment I mentioned.

22:59.934 --> 23:02.169
I want you to suffer.

23:03.938 --> 23:07.307
And I want you to pay
me until the day you die.

23:08.210 --> 23:10.043
How much?

23:10.045 --> 23:13.880
Half paid to me every month.

23:17.118 --> 23:19.919
All right. Half my salary.

23:20.922 --> 23:23.557
And half of everything you steal, skim,

23:23.558 --> 23:26.259
and ferret away.

23:31.199 --> 23:34.434
Over that, you can go fuck yourself.

23:34.569 --> 23:38.038
And I'd advise you to find someone
else that wants to fuck you, too,

23:38.073 --> 23:40.540
because I'm only paying for five years.

23:40.541 --> 23:42.943
After that,

23:42.944 --> 23:45.012
you're on your own.

23:45.080 --> 23:48.114
So start casting about
for men with deep pockets,

23:48.115 --> 23:51.150
poor eyesight, and very little need

23:51.151 --> 23:53.519
for proper sexual gratification.

24:10.470 --> 24:12.371
I've sped up the crews

24:12.439 --> 24:16.242
and I believe we'll
soon be back on schedule.

24:16.243 --> 24:18.477
Are you sure that's wise?

24:18.478 --> 24:20.912
To rush the crews?

24:20.913 --> 24:23.481
Perhaps we should slow them a bit.

24:23.482 --> 24:26.017
I worry about accidents.

24:26.085 --> 24:28.854
As do I, which is why there won't be any.

24:28.855 --> 24:31.256
He won't cooperate.

24:31.257 --> 24:33.625
He's a by-the-book operator.

24:33.626 --> 24:36.394
He's cutting costs.

24:36.495 --> 24:39.664
Wants to bring the project in
under budget from here on out.

24:39.698 --> 24:41.933
- What kind of fruit does that?
- Exactly.

24:41.968 --> 24:45.102
So, we have our normal arrangement?

24:45.203 --> 24:48.806
Look, Herm, I could bust the
guy up, but what's the point?

24:48.807 --> 24:50.174
The building's nearly done.

24:50.175 --> 24:52.109
Let's at least slow it down.

24:52.144 --> 24:54.311
We got to let it get built sometime.

24:54.379 --> 24:56.046
If we didn't, they
wouldn't build the next one

24:56.047 --> 24:57.448
and we couldn't skim off that.

24:57.482 --> 25:01.051
There is no next one. This is it for me.

25:01.052 --> 25:03.287
I have expenses, Jimmy.

25:03.354 --> 25:05.422
You might pull a few more
bucks out of the building,

25:05.490 --> 25:08.024
but short of finding a
way to turn back the clock

25:08.026 --> 25:09.993
and start the whole project over again,

25:09.995 --> 25:11.996
I'd say find another scheme.

25:11.997 --> 25:13.797
I am not giving up.

25:13.832 --> 25:16.167
There are a lot more ways to game this

25:16.168 --> 25:18.302
and I will find them.

25:18.303 --> 25:19.969
I wish you luck, Herm.

25:20.004 --> 25:22.505
And when you do, don't forget our cut.

25:22.506 --> 25:24.173
Yeah.

